  "text": "Prevalence of oral anti-diabetic drug prescribing by age groups and country with 95% confidence interval in seven European countries. Aged 0-1 ( ); aged 2-5 ( ); aged 6-11 ( ); aged 12-18 ( ) (0.012%). The UK stood out with the highest prevalence of oral anti-diabetics (0.36 per 1000), followed by Italy (0.24 per 1000). The most frequently prescribed oral antidiabetic in all countries was metformin. Metformin is currently licensed in most countries for the treatment of type 2 diabetes in children above 10 years of age; however, it is also increasingly used off label for the treatment of polycystic ovarian syndrome and obesity [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Hsia et al.",
